  "concept": "Concentration (ppm)",
  "question": {
    "text": "Q1. A water sample contains 0.002 g of lead (Pb²⁺) dissolved in 500 L of water.\nAssuming the density of water = 1 g mL⁻¹, calculate the concentration of lead in ppm.\nUse the relation:\nppm = mass of solute / total mass of solution × 10⁶\nAlso, for dilute aqueous solutions:\n1 ppm ≈ 1 mg L⁻¹",
    "image": null
  },
  "options": [
