  "concept": "Molarity and Strength",
  "question": {
    "text": "A solution of H₂SO₄ has a molarity of 0.25 mol L⁻¹. The molar mass of H₂SO₄ = 98 g mol⁻¹. A chemist prepares 2 L of this solution. Calculate the mass of H₂SO₄ required.",
    "image": null
  },
  "options": [
    { "id": "a", "text": "24.5 g" },
    { "id": "b", "text": "49 g" },
    { "id": "c", "text": "98 g" },
    { "id": "d", "text": "196 g" }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "b",
  "solution": {
    "text": "\\( \\text{Strength} = M \\times \\text{Molar Mass} \\)",
    "image": null
  },
  "solution_steps": [
    "Step 1: Calculate strength of solution",
    "\\( \\text{Strength} = 0.25 \\times 98 \\)",
    "\\( = 24.5\\,g\\,L^{-1} \\)",

    "Step 2: Use strength relation",
    "\\( \\text{Strength} = \\frac{\\text{mass}}{\\text{volume}} \\)",

    "Step 3: Substitute values",
    "\\( 24.5 = \\frac{\\text{mass}}{2} \\)",

    "Step 4: Calculate mass",
    "\\( \\text{mass} = 24.5 \\times 2 \\)",
    "\\( = 49\\,g \\)",

    "Final Answer: \\(49\\,g\\)"
  ]
},
  {
  "code": "IN12C18T1Q3",
  "concept": "Normality",
  "question": {
    "text": "Q3. A solution is prepared by dissolving \\(4.9\\,g\\) of \\(H_2SO_4\\) to make \\(500\\,mL\\) of solution.\n(Molar mass of \\(H_2SO_4 = 98\\,g\\,mol^{-1}\\))\nCalculate the normality of the solution.",
    "image": null
  },
  "options": [
    { "id": "a", "text": "0.10 N" },
    { "id": "b", "text": "0.20 N" },
    { "id": "c", "text": "0.40 N" },
    { "id": "d", "text": "0.50 N" }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "b",
  "solution": {
    "text": "\\[N = \\frac{\\text{Weight of solute}}{\\text{Equivalent weight} \\times \\text{Volume}}\\]",
    "image": null
  },
  "solution_steps": [
    "Step 1: Write formula",
    "\\[N = \\frac{\\text{Weight}}{\\text{Equivalent weight} \\times \\text{Volume}}\\]",

    "Step 2: Determine n-factor",
    "For \\(H_2SO_4\\), it donates \\(2H^+\\), so \\(n = 2\\)",

    "Step 3: Calculate equivalent weight",
    "\\[\\text{Equivalent weight} = \\frac{98}{2} = 49\\]",

    "Step 4: Convert volume",
    "\\[500\\,mL = 0.5\\,L\\]",

    "Step 5: Substitute values",
    "\\[N = \\frac{4.9}{49 \\times 0.5}\\]",

    "Step 6: Solve",
    "\\[N = \\frac{4.9}{24.5}\\]",
    "\\[N = 0.20\\]",

    "Final Answer: 0.20 N"
  ]
},
